.TH BT-JOY 1 "2026-05-18" "bt-joy 0.0.6" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bt-joy \- read joystick input and send UDP RC channel frames
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bt-joy
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bt-joy
reads a Linux joystick device, maps axes and buttons to RC channel values,
and sends those values as UDP packets to a bt-joy server.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-config FILE
Load joystick client configuration from FILE. The packaged service uses
.IR /etc/bt-joy/client.yaml .
.TP
.B \-\-mapping FILE
Override the joystick channel mapping YAML configured by the client config.
.TP
.B \-\-device PATH
Override the joystick device path.
.TP
.B \-\-host HOST
Override the UDP destination host.
.TP
.B \-\-port PORT
Override the UDP destination port.
.TP
.B \-\-poll-hz HZ
Override joystick polling frequency.
.TP
.B \-\-keepalive-interval SECONDS
Override seconds between UDP keepalive requests. Use 0 to disable.
.TP
.B \-\-keepalive-timeout SECONDS
Override seconds to wait before logging a missing keepalive response.
.TP
.B \-\-joystick-reconnect-interval SECONDS
Override seconds to wait before retrying a missing or disconnected joystick.
.TP
.B \-\-log-mapping
Log joystick state and mapped channel values.
.TP
.B \-\-log-level LEVEL
Set log verbosity.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/bt-joy/client.yaml
Default service configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/bt-joy/mapping.yaml
Default joystick channel mapping.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bt-joy-client.yaml (5),
.BR bt-joy-client.service (8),
.BR joy-server (1)
